-- Veolia’s Bucharest Unit Seeking Bids for Water Pipeline
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-04-12T09:40:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-12/veolia-s-bucharest-unit-seeking-bids-for-water-pipeline.html
The Romanian utility  Apa Nova
Bucuresti SA,  a subsidiary of the French water company  Veolia
Environnement SA (VIE) , is seeking bids for pipeline design services
in the capital.  Bids for the Bucharest contract estimated at 6.8 million
lei ($2 million) will be accepted until May 13, according to  a
notice  published today on the European Union’s tender website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Randall Hackley at 
 rhackley@bloomberg.net  